SUMMARY:Lawrence of Arabia | 15 Years\, 15 Hits
DESCRIPTION:Arguably one of the best films ever made\, David Lean's story
  depicts the life of T.E. Lawrence\, the controversial and romanticized B
 ritish officer who led an Arab revolt against the Ottoman Empire during t
 he First World War. Starring a cast that includes Peter O'Toole as Lawren
 ce\, Alec Guinness\, Omar Sharif\, Claude Rains\, Anthony Quinn\, and Jos
 é Ferrer (who once said\, "If I was to be judged by any one film perform
 ance\, it would be my five minutes in Lawrence")\, and nominated for 10 A
 cademy Awards with seven wins\, Lawrence of Arabia was the first film eve
 r screened at IU Cinema when it first opened 15 years ago in 2011. [227 m
 in\; drama\, adventure\; English\, Arabic\, and Turkish]
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Arguably one of the best films ever mad
 e\, David Lean's story depicts the life of T.E. Lawrence\, the controvers
 ial and romanticized British officer who led an Arab revolt against the O
 ttoman Empire during the First World War. Starring a cast that includes P
 eter O'Toole as Lawrence\, Alec Guinness\, Omar Sharif\, Claude Rains\, A
 nthony Quinn\, and José Ferrer (who once said\, "If I was to be judged b
 y any one film performance\, it would be my five minutes in <i>Lawrence</
 i>")\, and nominated for 10 Academy Awards with seven wins\, <i>Lawrence 
 of Arabia</i> was the first film ever screened at IU Cinema when it first
  opened 15 years ago in 2011. [227 min\; drama\, adventure\; English\, Ar
 abic\, and Turkish]</p>
